The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 30: India and Switzerland have signed a treaty that will enable exchange of information on tax evaders and give details of unaccounted funds stashed away by Indians in Swiss banks. The treaty is a revised version of the existing double taxation avoidance agreement and was signed by Swiss foreign minister Micheline Calmy-Rey and finance minister Pranab Mukherjee.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 30: The Supreme Court today issued notices to former Satyam managing director B. Rama Raju and four others, accused in the Satyam case, asking why their bails should not be cancelled. The apex court has directed them to file their reply within a week.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 30: Videocon is in talks with foreign entities for a 26 per cent stake sale in its telecom subsidiary Videocon Telecommunications. We are looking for a total valuation of Rs 15,000 crore, Videocon chairman V.N. Dhoot said.                             
	 Mumbai, Aug. 30: Punjab National Bank has increased its fixed deposit rate by 25 basis points on select maturities. The bank has realigned the rate of interest on retail term deposit from September 1 on two slabs.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 30: Glenmark Pharmaceuticals has discovered a drug molecule, which can be used for treating pain and respiratory disorders. The new drug molecule has completed pre-clinical trials.                                                                                                                          
